<title>UK: UBS sets $250 million five-year convertible bond. [CORRECTED 8:03 GMT]</title>
<headline>UBS sets $250 million five-year convertible bond. [CORRECTED 8:03 GMT]</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-05-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>(Corrects title from &quot;six-year convertible bond&quot;)</p>
<p>The following convertible bond was announced by lead manager UBS Ltd.</p>
<p> BORROWER   UNION BANK OF SWITZERLAND</p>
<p> AMT	  $250 MLN  COUPON    *2.75-3.00 MATURITY    16.JUN.02</p>
<p> TYPE    CONVERTIBLE  ISS PRICE  PAR	 PAY DATE    16.JUN.97</p>
<p> NOTES     *TO BE PRICED LATER.</p>
<p>		CONVERSION PREMIUM INDICATED AT 23-25 PERCENT.</p>
<p> MOODY/S&amp;P  AAA/AA+   LISTING    LUX	 SALE LIMITS =</p>
<p> NOTES	CALLABLE AFTER TWO YEARS AT PAR SUBJECT TO 130 PCT</p>
<p>		HURDLE. CALLABLE AFTER THREE YEARS AT 102 AND AFTER</p>
<p>		FOUR YEARS AT 101.</p>
<p>-- London Newsroom +44 171 542 7658</p>
